{"type":"message","id":"25f0c57e","parentId":"53973c28","timestamp":"2026-04-21T03:08:08.034Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I need a more systematic approach to extract all app_id to application name mappings. Let me write a small extraction script that processes the file line by line and captures the relationship between app_id numbers and their corresponding names/descriptions.\n\nThe pattern seems to be:\n1. `local app_id=\"X\"` - defines the number\n2. `local panelname=\"Name\"` or description nearby\n3. Sometimes there's a local lujing check condition\n\nLet me extract these pairs more carefully.\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"796325666","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# 写一个更系统的提取方法\npython3 << 'PYEOF'\nimport re\n\nwith open('/usr/local/bin/k', 'r') as f:\n    content = f.read()\n\n# Find the linux_panel section\nstart = content.find('linux_panel() {')\nif start == -1:\n    print(\"Not found\")\n    exit(1)\n\nsection = content[start:start+50000]  # First 50K chars after function\n\n# Pattern to find app_id definitions and their associated names\npattern = r'local\\s+app_id=\"(\\d+)\"\\s*\\n\\s*local\\s+lujing=\"[^\"]+\"\\s*\\n\\s*local\\s+panelname=\"([^\"]+)\"'\nmatches = re.findall(pattern, section)\n\nfor i, (num, name) in enumerate(matches):\n    print(f\"{i+1}. 编号 {num}: {name}\")\nPYEOF"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"lmstudio","model":"qwen3.6-35b-a3b-claude-4.6-opus-reasoning-distilled@q4_k_m","usage":{"input":51816,"output":435,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":52251,"cost":{"input":0.103632,"output":0.00522,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.108852}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776740877267,"responseId":"chatcmpl-gg74qqoglfh6gcblyo07ij"}}
