{"type":"message","id":"6fd6e91a","parentId":"ef4911e2","timestamp":"2026-04-21T03:09:54.310Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The regex is matching the wrong things - it's picking up random Chinese characters instead of actual application names. Let me try a completely different approach. I'll look for the exact echo lines that contain both numbers and full Chinese text, then parse them line by line manually.\n\nLooking back at my earlier successful extraction:\n```\necho -e \"${gl_kjlan}1.   ${color1}宝塔面板官方版                      ${gl_kjlan}2.   \nThe approach should be to filter lines containing the specific pattern with numbered items and Chinese text, then extract those properly using a more reliable method than regex matching on individual characters. I'll need to adjust my strategy to capture complete application entries rather than fragmented pieces.\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"733558575","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python3 << 'PYEOF'\nimport re\n\nwith open('/usr/local/bin/k', 'r') as f:\n    lines = f.readlines()\n\n# Find the section with echo statements for application list\nin_app_list = False\napp_lines = []\n\nfor i, line in enumerate(lines):\n    # Look for the start of app list display\n    if \"应用市场\" in line and i < 16000:\n        in_app_list = True\n    \n    # If we're looking at echo lines with application numbers (Chinese + digits)\n    if in_app_list and \"echo\" in line and re.search(r'\\d+\\.\\s*\\u4e00', line):\n        app_lines.append((i, line))\n\nprint(f\"找到 {len(app_lines)} 条应用列表行\")\nprint(\"=\" * 75)\n\n# Parse each line to extract number-name pairs\nfor idx, (line_num, line) in enumerate(app_lines):\n    # Extract all \"N. Name\" patterns from the line\n    pattern = r'(\\d+)\\.\\s*\\S*\\s*([\\u4e00-\\u9fff\\w\\s\\.\\-]+?)\\s*(?:\\$\\{|\")'\n    \n    # Simpler: just find digit followed by period and Chinese text\n    simpler_pattern = r'(\\d+)\\.\\s*(.*?)(?:\\s+\\$\\{|\\s*\"[a-z]|$)'\n    matches = re.findall(simpler_pattern, line)\n    \n    if matches:\n        for num_str, name in matches:\n            # Clean up the name\n            name = name.strip()\n            # Skip if it's not a real application entry (too short or wrong format)\n            if len(name) > 3 and re.search(r'\\u4e00', name):\n                print(f\"行{line_num}: {num_str:>3}. {name}\")\n\nPYEOF"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"lmstudio","model":"qwen3.6-35b-a3b-claude-4.6-opus-reasoning-distilled@q4_k_m","usage":{"input":59440,"output":738,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":60178,"cost":{"input":0.11888,"output":0.008856000000000001,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.127736}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776740975063,"responseId":"chatcmpl-n996ady5qgzps9vd68yh"}}
